notesStmt.note: Title from title page (f. iii recto).

msContents.summary: A treatise on Aristotle's Physics, summarizing the Physics and breaking them down into more organized and manageable sections. All sections are titled and numbered. Divided into books, which are divided into arguments, which are then divided into articles or inquiries.

supportDesc.extent: 372 leaves : 200 x 160 (155 x 125) mm. bound to 210 x 165 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 372 leaves; [i-iii], 1-9,11-154,156-199, 201-261, 263-299, 301-399, 401-499, 501-599, 601-745; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive book script.

binding.p: Contemporary parchment with gilt arms of Hans Herwarth (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Hans-Heinrich Herwarth von Bittenfeld (coat of arms, upper cover).
